Preamble

The ItryPublic License (IPL) is designed to facilitate the free use, modification, and distribution of software while protecting the rights of the original authors.
1. Definitions

    Source Code: The human-readable form of the software.
    Object Code: The form of the software intended for execution on a computer.
    Derivative Work: Any work based on the Source Code, including modifications and translations.

2. Grant of Rights

    Right to Use: Licensee is granted the right to use the software for any purpose.
    Right to Modify: Licensee is granted the right to modify the Source Code to create Derivative Works.
    Right to Distribute: Licensee is granted the right to distribute the Source Code, Object Code, and Derivative Works.

3. Distribution Conditions

    Attribution: All copies or Derivative Works must include attribution information and copyright notices.
    License Inclusion: The text of the IPL must be included with any distribution.
    Source Code Availability: When distributing Object Code, the Source Code must also be made available or accessible.

4. Restrictions

    Removal of Notices: It is prohibited to remove or alter copyright notices and license information.
    Liability: The Licensor is not liable for any damages or losses resulting from the use of the software.

5. Patents

    Patent Rights: Licensor grants Licensee a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free patent license to the extent necessary to use, modify, and distribute the software.

6. Termination

    Violation of Terms: The license automatically terminates in the event of a violation of its terms.
    Reinstatement: The Licensee may reinstate the license by curing the violation.

7. Miscellaneous

    Jurisdiction: Any disputes arising from this license shall be resolved in accordance with the laws of the Russian Federation.
    Language: The official language of this license is English.
